getFirstMinimalConversionsFrom

public AutomatonType[] getFirstMinimalConversionsFrom(AutomatonType src)
Returns the first minimal conversions from an automaton of a specified source type to an equivalent automaton of this type. If the conversion is possible, an array of types {t1, t2, ..., tn} will be returned such that t1 is the source automaton type, tn is this automaton type, and direct conversions from ti to ti+1 are supported.

Parameters:
src - the source automaton type
Returns:
the minimal conversions from an automaton of a specified source type to an equivalent automaton of this type, or an empty array is the conversion is not supported

convert

public Automaton convert(Automaton aut)
Converts an automaton into this type with default conversion options. Note that this method wraps an UnsupportedException in an IllegalArgumentException.

Parameters:
aut - the automaton to be converted
Returns:
the equivalent automaton of this type, or maybe a larger (in language) automaton if this type is NCW or DCW
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the conversion is not supported or the input automaton is not valid

convert

public Automaton convert(Automaton aut,
                         Properties options)
Converts an automaton into this type with custom conversion options. The first minimal conversion sequence will be applied. Note that this method wraps an UnsupportedException in an IllegalArgumentException.

Parameters:
aut - the automaton to be converted
options - custom conversion options
Returns:
the equivalent automaton of this type, or maybe a larger (in language) automaton if this type is NCW or DCW
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the conversion is not supported or the input automaton is not valid
